			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://lightroomkillertips.com/files/2007/10/preset1.jpg" class="post_thumb" />This week, Laura (from <a href="http://www.lightroompresets.com" target="_blank">Pretty Presets</a>) was kind enough to donate some more free presets for me to give away. The images below show the before/after samples of the 2 presets included in the download below (from the Spring Color, Flare &amp; Haze Collection). If you like &#8216;em, she’s got plenty more available over at at Lightroompresets.com so make sure you stop by and pay her a visit.</p>
<p>The Spring Color, Flare &amp; Haze Collection was designed to add a sun-kissed touch to your natural light images. They&#8217;ll work best on your RAW images and were designed for both Lightroom 3 and 4, as you&#8217;ll see in the download below.<br />
(Special thanks to Spanki Mills and Jen Carver for the beautiful examples provided)</p>
<p>You can find out more about the presets and the entire collection over at her website (<a href="http://www.lightroompresets.com" target="_blank">www.lightroompresets.com</a>) or facebook page (<a href="http://www.facebook.com/PrettyPresets" target="_blank">www.facebook.com/PrettyPresets</a>)</p>
