		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdobeLightroomKillerTips/~3/C3fVqM1tnis/</link>
		<comments>http://lightroomkillertips.com/2012/lightroom-news-and-stuff/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 04 May 2012 15:23:54 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>jgilbert@photoshopuser.com (Matt Kloskowski)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://lightroomkillertips.com/?p=4206</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[A new date was just added to my Lightroom 4 Live tour. We&#8217;ll be in Lansing MI on June 12th. It also looks like we&#8217;ll be in [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://lightroomkillertips.com/files/2012/05/kickass.jpg"><img src="http://lightroomkillertips.com/files/2012/05/kickass.jpg" alt="" width="563" height="289" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4207" /></a></p>
<ul>
<li>A new <a href="http://kelbytraining.com/tours/adobe-photoshop-lightroom-4-live/" target="_blank">date was just added to my Lightroom 4 Live</a> tour. We&#8217;ll be in Lansing MI on June 12th. It also looks like we&#8217;ll be in Washing DC that same week and probably San Francisco the week after but I&#8217;ll keep you posted. </li>
<li><a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/lightroomjournal/2012/04/lightroom-4-1-rc2-now-available-on-adobe-labs.html" target="_blank">Lightroom 4.1 Release Candidate 2</a> is on the Adobe Labs website. If you had any problems with Lightroom 4, it&#8217;s definitely worth downloading. </li>
<p>Lightroom Product Manager, Tom Hogarty, has a great <a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/lightroomjournal/2012/04/new-color-fringe-correction-controls.html" target="_blank">write up about some of the new Color Fringe Correction features</a> in Lightroom 4</p>
<li><a href="http://www.moosepeterson.com/blog/2012/04/23/ipad-bt-journal/" target="_blank">Moose Peterson&#8217;s BT Journal</a> is now available on the iPad.</li>
<li>Don&#8217;t forget about the Student Discount for the Google Plus Photographers Conference. It&#8217;s just $99 for students with the code&#8230; wait for it&#8230; GPLUSSTUD. Gotta love that promo code huh? <img src='http://lightroomkillertips.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </li>
<li>I&#8217;ve been getting a TON of questions on the difference between Photoshop (and Bridge) and Lightroom. If you&#8217;re still wondering if Lightroom is for you then check out the videos that Scott and I did called <a href="http://www.photoshopuser.com/lightroom" target="_blank">100 Ways that Lightroom Kick&#8217;s The Bridge&#8217;s Ass for Photographers</a>. </li>
</ul>
